<!-- <title>Previo a la unidad</title> -->
<!-- <title>Exploración</title> -->
<!-- <title component="metadata">Alineado con <xref ref="graVV-uniYY-secZZ" text="title"/></title> -->
<title component="metadata">Alineado con <xref ref="lec-VVVVVV" text="title"/></title>

<statement>
  <p>Lin coloreó parte de algunas tiras de fracciones. ¿Qué fracción de cada una coloreó? Explica cómo lo sabes.</p>
  <ol>
    <li>
      <line></line>
      <line>
        <image source="svg-source/tikz-file-151732">
          <shortdescription>Diagram. Rectangle partitioned into 2 parts, 1 part shaded.</shortdescription>
        </image>
      </line>
    </li>
    <li>
      <line></line>
      <line>
      <image source="svg-source/tikz-file-151733">
        <shortdescription>Diagram. Rectangle split into 2 unequal parts, one part shaded.</shortdescription>
      </image>
      </line>
    </li>
    <li>
      <line></line>
      <line>
      <image source="svg-source/tikz-file-151734">
        <shortdescription>Diagram. Rectangle partitioned into 2 unequal parts, 1 part shaded.</shortdescription>
      </image>
      </line>
    </li>
  </ol>
</statement>

<solution>
  <p>[++++++++++++++++++++]</p>
  <p>Sample responses:</p>
  <ol>
    <li>
      <p><m>\frac{1}{2}</m> , because there are two equal pieces, one shaded and one unshaded.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p><m>\frac{5}{6}</m> , because I lined up the fraction strip with the ones in my book and the missing piece is <m>\frac{1}{6}</m> so there are <m>\frac{5}{6}</m> shaded.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p><m>\frac{3}{8}</m> , I tried to line it up with my different fractions strips. It is more than <m>\frac{1}{4}</m> or <m>\frac{1}{3}</m> but less than <m>\frac{1}{2}</m> and it lined up with <m>\frac{3}{8}</m> .</p>
    </li>
  </ol>
</solution>

</exercise>
